.TH PLSCMAP0 3plplot  "August, 2007" "" "PLplot API"
.SH NAME
\fBplscmap0\fP - Set color map0 colors by 8-bit RGB
values 
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBplscmap0\fP(\fIr\fP, \fIg\fP, \fIb\fP, \fIncol0\fP)
.SH DESCRIPTION

.P
Set color map0 colors using 8-bit RGB values (see the PLplot documentation).  This sets the entire color map -- only as many colors as specified will be allocated. 
.P
Redacted form: \fBplscmap0(r, g, b, ncol0)\fP
.P
This function is used in examples 2,24. 
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fIr\fP (PLINT *, input) 
Pointer to array with set of unsigned 8-bit integers (0-255) representing the degree of red in the color. 
.TP
\fIg\fP (PLINT *, input) 
Pointer to array with set of unsigned 8-bit integers (0-255) representing the degree of green in the color. 
.TP
\fIb\fP (PLINT *, input) 
Pointer to array with set of unsigned 8-bit integers (0-255) representing the degree of blue in the color. 
.TP
\fIncol0\fP (PLINT, input) 
Number of items in the \fIr\fP, \fIg\fP, and \fIb\fP arrays. 

